   <LONGTEXTS>
    <item>
     <DOKIL>
      <ID>RE</ID>
      <OBJECT>ZSBTMP_GEN_TREE</OBJECT>
      <LANGU>E</LANGU>
      <TYP>E</TYP>
      <VERSION>0001</VERSION>
      <MASTERLANG>X</MASTERLANG>
      <TXTLINES>00021</TXTLINES>
      <DOKSTATE>R</DOKSTATE>
     </DOKIL>
     <HEAD>
      <TDOBJECT>DOKU</TDOBJECT>
      <TDNAME>ZSBTMP_GEN_TREE</TDNAME>
      <TDID>RE</TDID>
      <TDSPRAS>E</TDSPRAS>
      <TDFORM>S_DOCU_SHOW</TDFORM>
      <TDSTYLE>S_DOCUS1</TDSTYLE>
      <TDVERSION>00001</TDVERSION>
      <TDLINESIZE>072</TDLINESIZE>
     </HEAD>
     <LINES>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>U1</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>&amp;PURPOSE&amp;</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>The Generic Table Change Explorer is an interactive utility to search,</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>decode, and analyze database table changes (from table DBTABLOG) for</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>any table that is configured for logging in the system.</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>U1</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>&amp;INTEGRATION&amp;</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>It uses Run-Time Type Information (RTTI) to dynamically analyze the</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>table structure (P_TAB) and reconstruct the logged data from raw bytes</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>without requiring static definition of the target table.</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>U1</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>&amp;FEATURES&amp;</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>U2</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>&amp;SELECTION&amp;</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>You can filter the logs by Table Name (P_TAB) and Log Date (s_logdat).</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>Additional filters allow restricting by Log Key, modifying user,</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>Transaction Code (tcode), and Operation Type (optype; default 'U').</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>The checkbox 'Only actual changes' (P_REAL) filters out entries</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>where the values did not change (old value equals new value).</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>U2</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>&amp;OUTPUT&amp;</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>In online mode, a split-screen layout is displayed:</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>- Left Pane: A hierarchical tree of changes grouped by record key.</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>- Right Pane: A ALV Grid listing the history of changes for the</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>  selected node. It displays change icons, old/new values with color</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDLINE>  highlighting, and metadata (date, time, user, and transaction).</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
      <TLINE>
       <TDFORMAT>AS</TDFORMAT>
       <TDLINE>In background (batch) mode, a flat list of change logs is printed.</TDLINE>
      </TLINE>
     </LINES>
    </item>
    <item>
